    agreement applies as between you, the User, and Muhammad Ubaid for our apps,
    website, and services. Your agreement to comply with and be bound by these Terms
    and Conditions is deemed to occur upon your first use of our apps or our Website.
    If you do not agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions, you should stop
    using our apps or this Website immediately.\r\n\r\nNo part of our apps or this
    website is intended to constitute a contractual offer capable of acceptance.
    Your order constitutes a contractual offer, and our acceptance of that offer
    is deemed to occur upon our sending a dispatch email to you indicating that your
    order has been fulfilled and is on its way to you.\r\n\r\n1. Definitions and
    Interpretation\r\nIn this Agreement, the following terms shall have the following
    meanings:\r\n\r\n\u201CAccount\u201D \u2013 means collectively your Apple iTunes
    Store or Google Play Store account.\r\n\r\n\u201CContent\u201D \u2013 means any
    text, graphics, images, audio, video, software, data compilations, and any other
    form of information capable of being stored in a computer that appears on or
    forms part of this Website.\r\n\r\n\u201CMuhammad Ubaid\u201D \u2013 means Muhammad
    Ubaid, trading as Muhammad Ubaid.\r\n\r\n\u201CService\u201D \u2013 means collectively
    any online facilities, tools, services, or information that Muhammad Ubaid makes
    available through our apps or website either now or in the future.\r\n\r\n\u201CPayment
    Information\u201D \u2013 means any details required for the purchase of Services
    from this Website.\r\n\r\n\u201CPurchase Information\u201D \u2013 means collectively
    any orders, invoices, receipts, or similar that may be in hard copy or electronic
    form.\r\n\r\n\u201CSystem\u201D \u2013 means any online communications infrastructure
    that Muhammad Ubaid makes available through our App or Website.\r\n\r\n\u201CUser
    / Users\u201D \u2013 means any third party that accesses the Website and is not
    employed by Muhammad Ubaid and acting in the course of their employment.\r\n\r\n2.
    Intellectual Property\r\n2.1. Subject to the exceptions in Clause 3, all Content
    on our apps, website, and Services is the property of Muhammad Ubaid or relevant
    third parties and is protected by applicable intellectual property laws.\r\n\r\n2.2.
    Except as allowed under Clause 4, you may not reproduce or reuse material from
    our apps or website without express written permission.\r\n\r\n3. Third Party
    Intellectual Property\r\n3.1. All IP rights in product images and descriptions
    belong to the respective manufacturers or suppliers.\r\n\r\n3.2. You may not
    reproduce or reuse such material without permission from the relevant owners.\r\n\r\n4.
    Fair Use of Intellectual Property\r\nContent may be re-used without permission
    only as allowed under Chapter III of the Copyright Designs and Patents Act 1988.\r\n\r\n5.
    Links to Other Websites\r\nLinks on our site may lead to third-party sites not
    under our control. We are not responsible for their content or practices.\r\n\r\n6.
    Links to Our Website\r\nYou may only link to this Website with prior permission
    from Muhammad Ubaid. Deep linking requires express permission.\r\n\r\n7. Use
    of Communications Facilities\r\n7.1. When using our System, you must:\r\n\r\nNot
    use obscene or offensive language\r\n\r\nNot submit unlawful or harmful content\r\n\r\nNot
    impersonate others\r\n\r\nNot submit spam or mass communications\r\n\r\nSubmit
    in English where possible\r\n\r\n7.2. We reserve the right to monitor communications
    via our System.\r\n\r\n8. Accounts\r\n8.1. Our apps are free to play with limited
    access to content.\r\n8.2. Subscriptions are monthly.\r\n8.3. Payments are charged
    through iTunes or Google Play.\r\n8.4. Renewals are charged within 24 hours before
    the end of the current period.\r\n8.5. You can manage your subscription and turn
    off auto-renewal via Account Settings.\r\n8.6. Any unused free trial will be
    forfeited upon subscription purchase.\r\n\r\n9. Termination and Cancellation\r\n9.1.
    You can cancel your Account via Account Settings.\r\n9.4. Cancellations before
    the service starts may be eligible for refunds.\r\n9.5. Unused free trial periods
    are forfeited upon subscription purchase.\r\n\r\n10. Payment\r\n10.1. Payments
    are processed through your app store account.\r\n10.2. Renewals are processed
    within 24 hours of the current subscription ending.\r\n\r\n11. Services, Pricing,
    and Availability\r\n11.1. Prices may change and offers may be updated monthly.\r\n\r\n12.
    Provision of Services\r\n12.1. We aim to provide our services with reasonable
    skill and care.\r\n12.2. If a mistake occurs in your order, contact us within
    10 days. We\u2019ll resolve issues within 7 working days.\r\n\r\n13. Privacy\r\nOur
    Privacy Policy governs use of the Website and is incorporated into these Terms.\r\n\r\n14.
    Disclaimers\r\n14.1. We make no guarantee that the Website will meet your needs
    or be secure.\r\n14.2. Nothing on this Website is intended to constitute professional
    advice.\r\n\r\n15. Changes to Services and Terms\r\nWe reserve the right to change
    the Website, its Content, or these Terms at any time.\r\n\r\n16. Availability\r\nThe
    Service is provided \u201Cas is\u201D and \u201Cas available\u201D.\r\n\r\n17.
    Limitation of Liability\r\n17.1. We accept no liability for any direct or indirect
    loss or damage from use of our apps or website.\r\n17.2. This does not exclude
    liability for death or injury due to negligence or fraud.\r\n\r\n18. No Waiver\r\nFailure
    to enforce any right does not waive that right.\r\n\r\n19. Notices\r\nSend all
    communications to:\r\nEmail: ubaidshahid125@gmail.com\r\n\r\nMessages are deemed
    received the same day if on a business day or the next business day otherwise.\r\n\r\n20.
    Law and Jurisdiction\r\nThese Terms are governed by the laws of Pakistan. Any
    disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of Pakistani courts."
